parameters.description: Query the results.                                        Schema: key'OPERATOR'value. Separate multiple through ','. Embedded documents marked with a (dot).                                        Supported operators:                                        = (equals)                                        != (not equals)                                        > (greater than)                                        < (less than)                                        >= (greater than or equal)                                        <= (less than or equal)                                        * (string contains)                                         ! (string does not contains)                                            Example: name*John,address.street=1st Street -> finds everyone that has John in the name and live ins 1st Street

parameters.description: Query the results.                                        Schema: key'OPERATOR'value. Separate multiple through ','. Supported operators:                                        = (equals)                                        != (not equals)                                        > (greater than)                                        < (less than)                                        >= (greater than or equal)                                        <= (less than or equal)                                        * (string contains)                                         ! (string does not contains)                                            Example: name*John,address.street=1st Street -> finds everyone that has John in the name and live ins 1st Street

post.description:
Perform measurements on points within a specific snapshot.

Takes a list of points (either in global coordinates [lat/lon] or local coordinates [easting/northing])
and performs requested measurements. All points must use the same coordinate system.

Supported measurements:
- Individual point heights and coordinates
- Line measurements (2D/3D) - Requires min. 2 points
- Area measurements (2D/3D) - Requires min. 3 points
- Volume measurements - Requires min. 3 points
- Cross section measurements - Requires min. 2 points

All distance measurements are in meters, coordinates in degrees.

If a reference_terrain_id is provided, height differences to the reference terrain
will be included in point measurements where available.

Args:
    snapshot: The snapshot to measure in
    user: The authenticated user
    data: Measurement configuration including:
        - points: List of points to measure (all must use same coordinate system)
        - reference_terrain_id: Optional ID for height difference calculations
        - manipulated: Whether to use manipulated version of snapshot
        - line_config: Optional config for 2D/3D line measurements
        - area_config: Optional config for 2D/3D area measurements
        - volume_measurement_config: Optional config for volume calculations
        - cross_section_config: Optional config for cross section measurements

Returns:
    GenericResponse containing OutMeasurementResult with:
        - points: List of measured points with heights and optional reference differences
        - line_result: Optional 2D/3D lengths if requested
        - area_result: Optional 2D/3D areas if requested
        - volume_result: Optional positive/negative volumes if requested
        - cross_section_result: Optional cross section points if requested

parameters.description: Unique snapshot MongoDB Object-ID as string

schema.title: Unique snapshot MongoDB Object-ID as string
schema.description: Unique snapshot MongoDB Object-ID as string

parameters.name: snapshot_id
